<subSubSection pageId="67" pageNumber="68" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1437,812,1595]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<keyLead pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
1 Base of elytra markedly biarcuate; each elytron with traces of four costae; upperside and underside golden-green, the elytra with a specifically diagnostic blackish-lilac pattern (Fig. 129) 
<taxonomicName authority="Levey, 2012" authorityName="Levey" authorityYear="2012" box="[1280,1375,841,862]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Melobasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eximia" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1280,1375,841,862]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">M. eximia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1382,1436,840,861]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1382,1436,840,861]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1437,812,1595]" box="[157,1436,870,891]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<keyLead box="[157,1436,870,891]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">- Without the above combination of characters................................................................ 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1437,812,1595]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<keyLead pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
2 Mesoepisternum with numerous large round setae-bearing punctures (Fig. 44); elytra with two or three costae; elytra with well defined vittae and fasciae (
<figureCitation box="[482,564,929,950]" captionStart="FIGURES 132–141" captionStartId="95.[151,257,1717,1738]" captionTargetBox="[229,1369,198,1676]" captionTargetId="figure-118@95.[172,1417,191,1704]" captionTargetPageId="95" captionText="FIGURES 132–141. dorsal habitus of Melobasis spp. gloriosa species group: M. gloriosa gloriosa (Laporte &amp; Gory): 132–138: 132. ♀, Lake Lockhart, 17 km S. of Newdegate, W.A.; 133. ♀, 42 km S.W. of Beverley, W.A.; 134. ♂, Mt. Dale, W.A.; 135. ♂, Mt. Dale, W.A.; 136. ♂, 5 km S. of Kirup, W.A.; 137. ♀, Mt. Dale, W.A.; 138–139: M. gloriosa cruentata Thomson: 138. ♀, Berkshire Park, N.S.W.; 139. ♂, Lapstone Hill, N.S.W.; 140. M. similis sp. n. (paratype, Wurarga, W.A.); 141. M. robusta Carter (Wurarga, W.A.). Scale bars = 5.0 mm." pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Fig. 140</figureCitation>
)........................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Levey, 2012" authorityName="Levey" authorityYear="2012" box="[1281,1376,929,950]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Melobasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1281,1376,929,950]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">M. similis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1382,1436,928,949]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1382,1436,928,949]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1437,812,1595]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<keyLead pageId="67" pageNumber="68">- Mesoepisternum without or with very few large round setae-bearing punctures, but with few to many small non setae-bearing punctures; elytra usually with at most only one costa; elytra with or without well defined vittae and fasciae.............. 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1437,812,1595]" box="[151,1435,1017,1038]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<keyLead box="[151,1435,1017,1038]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
3 Large, robust, entirely brown-bronze species (
<figureCitation box="[666,750,1017,1038]" captionStart="FIGURES 132–141" captionStartId="95.[151,257,1717,1738]" captionTargetBox="[229,1369,198,1676]" captionTargetId="figure-118@95.[172,1417,191,1704]" captionTargetPageId="95" captionText="FIGURES 132–141. dorsal habitus of Melobasis spp. gloriosa species group: M. gloriosa gloriosa (Laporte &amp; Gory): 132–138: 132. ♀, Lake Lockhart, 17 km S. of Newdegate, W.A.; 133. ♀, 42 km S.W. of Beverley, W.A.; 134. ♂, Mt. Dale, W.A.; 135. ♂, Mt. Dale, W.A.; 136. ♂, 5 km S. of Kirup, W.A.; 137. ♀, Mt. Dale, W.A.; 138–139: M. gloriosa cruentata Thomson: 138. ♀, Berkshire Park, N.S.W.; 139. ♂, Lapstone Hill, N.S.W.; 140. M. similis sp. n. (paratype, Wurarga, W.A.); 141. M. robusta Carter (Wurarga, W.A.). Scale bars = 5.0 mm." pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Fig. 141</figureCitation>
); length 
<quantity box="[833,931,1017,1038]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.1" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" unit="mm" value="17.5" valueMax="21.0" valueMin="14.0">14–21mm</quantity>
............................ 
<taxonomicName authority="Carter" authorityName="Carter" box="[1261,1435,1017,1038]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Melobasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robusta">
<emphasis box="[1261,1369,1017,1038]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">M. robusta</emphasis>
Carter
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1437,812,1595]" box="[151,1436,1046,1067]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1046,1067]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
- Smaller, less robust species, very variable in colour and markings; length 
<quantity box="[932,1021,1046,1067]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" unit="mm" value="11.0" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="8.0">8–14mm</quantity>
.................................. 4
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1437,812,1595]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<keyLead pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
4 Lateral half of pronotum clothed with fairly long conspicuous pubescence; mesoepisternum shiny, mirror like, unpunctured except at the margins; underside densely clothed with long conspicuous pubescence; uniformly greyish bronze (Fig. 131)........................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="Levey, 2012" authorityName="Levey" authorityYear="2012" box="[1245,1376,1134,1155]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Melobasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="specularis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1245,1376,1134,1155]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">M. specularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1382,1436,1134,1155]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1382,1436,1134,1155]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1437,812,1595]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<keyLead pageId="67" pageNumber="68">- Lateral half of pronotum glabrous or with pubescence only close to the lateral carina, without the other characteristics combined............................................................................................... 5</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1437,812,1595]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<keyLead pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
5 Underside densely clothed with long pubescence, particularly conspicuous on the prosternal process; narrow species (Fig. 130); aedeagus very elongate (
<figureCitation box="[518,600,1252,1273]" captionStart="FIGURES 191–195" captionStartId="103.[151,258,1904,1925]" captionTargetBox="[268,1345,217,1874]" captionTargetId="figure-71@103.[220,1371,191,1891]" captionTargetPageId="103" captionText="FIGURES 191–195. Melobasis spp. gloriosa species group aedeagi: 191. M. specularis sp. n. (paratype, Lake Campion, W.A.); 192. M. angusta sp. n. (paratype, Merredin, W.A.); 193. M. gloriosa gloriosa (Laporte &amp; Gory) (Mt. Dale, W.A.); 194. M. gloriosa cruentata Thomson (Sydney, N.S.W.); 195. M. eximia sp. n. (holotype, Tennant Creek–Newcastle Waters, N. T.). Scale bars = 1.0 mm." pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Fig. 192</figureCitation>
)....................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Levey, 2012" authorityName="Levey" authorityYear="2012" box="[1268,1376,1252,1273]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Melobasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angusta" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1268,1376,1252,1273]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">M. angusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1382,1436,1251,1272]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1382,1436,1251,1272]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1437,812,1595]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<keyLead pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
- Underside usually less densely clothed with shorter pubescence; less narrow species (
<figureCitation box="[1056,1199,1281,1302]" captionStart="FIGURES 132–141" captionStartId="95.[151,257,1717,1738]" captionTargetBox="[229,1369,198,1676]" captionTargetId="figure-118@95.[172,1417,191,1704]" captionTargetPageId="95" captionText="FIGURES 132–141. dorsal habitus of Melobasis spp. gloriosa species group: M. gloriosa gloriosa (Laporte &amp; Gory): 132–138: 132. ♀, Lake Lockhart, 17 km S. of Newdegate, W.A.; 133. ♀, 42 km S.W. of Beverley, W.A.; 134. ♂, Mt. Dale, W.A.; 135. ♂, Mt. Dale, W.A.; 136. ♂, 5 km S. of Kirup, W.A.; 137. ♀, Mt. Dale, W.A.; 138–139: M. gloriosa cruentata Thomson: 138. ♀, Berkshire Park, N.S.W.; 139. ♂, Lapstone Hill, N.S.W.; 140. M. similis sp. n. (paratype, Wurarga, W.A.); 141. M. robusta Carter (Wurarga, W.A.). Scale bars = 5.0 mm." pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Figs. 132–139</figureCitation>
); aedeagus less elongate (
<figureCitation box="[232,371,1310,1331]" captionStart="FIGURES 191–195" captionStartId="103.[151,258,1904,1925]" captionTargetBox="[268,1345,217,1874]" captionTargetId="figure-71@103.[220,1371,191,1891]" captionTargetPageId="103" captionText="FIGURES 191–195. Melobasis spp. gloriosa species group aedeagi: 191. M. specularis sp. n. (paratype, Lake Campion, W.A.); 192. M. angusta sp. n. (paratype, Merredin, W.A.); 193. M. gloriosa gloriosa (Laporte &amp; Gory) (Mt. Dale, W.A.); 194. M. gloriosa cruentata Thomson (Sydney, N.S.W.); 195. M. eximia sp. n. (holotype, Tennant Creek–Newcastle Waters, N. T.). Scale bars = 1.0 mm." pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Figs. 193, 194</figureCitation>
)....................................................................................... 6
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1437,812,1595]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<keyLead pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
6 Subspecies from 
<collectingRegion box="[397,579,1340,1361]" country="Australia" name="New South Wales" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">New South Wales</collectingRegion>
; consistently sexually dichromatic, females entirely brown- or grey-bronze (
<figureCitation box="[1346,1424,1340,1361]" captionStart="FIGURES 132–141" captionStartId="95.[151,257,1717,1738]" captionTargetBox="[229,1369,198,1676]" captionTargetId="figure-118@95.[172,1417,191,1704]" captionTargetPageId="95" captionText="FIGURES 132–141. dorsal habitus of Melobasis spp. gloriosa species group: M. gloriosa gloriosa (Laporte &amp; Gory): 132–138: 132. ♀, Lake Lockhart, 17 km S. of Newdegate, W.A.; 133. ♀, 42 km S.W. of Beverley, W.A.; 134. ♂, Mt. Dale, W.A.; 135. ♂, Mt. Dale, W.A.; 136. ♂, 5 km S. of Kirup, W.A.; 137. ♀, Mt. Dale, W.A.; 138–139: M. gloriosa cruentata Thomson: 138. ♀, Berkshire Park, N.S.W.; 139. ♂, Lapstone Hill, N.S.W.; 140. M. similis sp. n. (paratype, Wurarga, W.A.); 141. M. robusta Carter (Wurarga, W.A.). Scale bars = 5.0 mm." pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Fig.138</figureCitation>
); males with the head and underside entirely golden-green, pronotum golden-green with a pair of coppery or purple-brown admedian vittae in the basal two-thirds, elytra coppery or purple-brown with the suture in the basal fifth and a broad oblique vitta extending from the base almost to the apex golden-green, (sometimes the vitta is divided just behind the middle) (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 132–141" captionStartId="95.[151,257,1717,1738]" captionTargetBox="[229,1369,198,1676]" captionTargetId="figure-118@95.[172,1417,191,1704]" captionTargetPageId="95" captionText="FIGURES 132–141. dorsal habitus of Melobasis spp. gloriosa species group: M. gloriosa gloriosa (Laporte &amp; Gory): 132–138: 132. ♀, Lake Lockhart, 17 km S. of Newdegate, W.A.; 133. ♀, 42 km S.W. of Beverley, W.A.; 134. ♂, Mt. Dale, W.A.; 135. ♂, Mt. Dale, W.A.; 136. ♂, 5 km S. of Kirup, W.A.; 137. ♀, Mt. Dale, W.A.; 138–139: M. gloriosa cruentata Thomson: 138. ♀, Berkshire Park, N.S.W.; 139. ♂, Lapstone Hill, N.S.W.; 140. M. similis sp. n. (paratype, Wurarga, W.A.); 141. M. robusta Carter (Wurarga, W.A.). Scale bars = 5.0 mm." pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Fig. 139</figureCitation>
); elytra usually with a well defined costa lateral to the subsutural depression, and sometimes traces of a second; punctation of elytra lateral to the costa with scarcely any indications of seriation.................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Thomson" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1879" box="[1129,1436,1486,1507]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Melobasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="gloriosa" subSpecies="cruentata">
<emphasis box="[1129,1339,1486,1507]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">M. gloriosa cruentata</emphasis>
Thomson
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1437,812,1595]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<keyLead pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
- Subspecies from W. 
<collectingCountry box="[433,524,1516,1537]" name="Australia" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Australia</collectingCountry>
; colour and markings very variable, not consistently sexually dichromatic (
<figureCitation box="[1280,1425,1516,1537]" captionStart="FIGURES 132–141" captionStartId="95.[151,257,1717,1738]" captionTargetBox="[229,1369,198,1676]" captionTargetId="figure-118@95.[172,1417,191,1704]" captionTargetPageId="95" captionText="FIGURES 132–141. dorsal habitus of Melobasis spp. gloriosa species group: M. gloriosa gloriosa (Laporte &amp; Gory): 132–138: 132. ♀, Lake Lockhart, 17 km S. of Newdegate, W.A.; 133. ♀, 42 km S.W. of Beverley, W.A.; 134. ♂, Mt. Dale, W.A.; 135. ♂, Mt. Dale, W.A.; 136. ♂, 5 km S. of Kirup, W.A.; 137. ♀, Mt. Dale, W.A.; 138–139: M. gloriosa cruentata Thomson: 138. ♀, Berkshire Park, N.S.W.; 139. ♂, Lapstone Hill, N.S.W.; 140. M. similis sp. n. (paratype, Wurarga, W.A.); 141. M. robusta Carter (Wurarga, W.A.). Scale bars = 5.0 mm." pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Figs. 132–137</figureCitation>
); elytra sometimes with, however, often without a well defined costa lateral to the subsutural depression; punctation in central third of elytra usually partly seriate.......................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="gloriosa (Laporte &amp; Gory)" baseAuthorityName="Laporte &amp; Gory" box="[1057,1436,1574,1595]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Melobasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="gloriosa" subSpecies="gloriosa">
<emphasis box="[1057,1260,1574,1595]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">M. gloriosa gloriosa</emphasis>
(Laporte &amp; Gory)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
